There are 2 methods to go for PPT to Image/PDF in Python 

First Method : Commercial Python library named as aspose.slides.
              Aspose.Slides is a powerful library for working with PowerPoint files in Python. 
              It provides comprehensive functionality for creating, reading, manipulating, and converting PowerPoint presentations (both PPT and PPTX formats)

Second Method : Using LibreOffice in Headless Mode - You can use LibreOffice in headless mode directly. This requires LibreOffice to be installed on your system. You can call LibreOffice from the command line or from within a Python script.
